data.name: Crispy Crab Cakes with Zesty Remoulade Sauce
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously crispy crab cakes paired with a zesty homemade remoulade sauce for a perfect seafood delight!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large bowl, combine crab meat, mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, and egg.
Gently fold in breadcrumbs, green onions, parsley, salt, pepper, and paprika until mixed.
Form the mixture into small patties (about 2-3 inches in diameter).
Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Fry the crab cakes for about 4-5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Serve hot with zesty remoulade sauce on the side.
